Welcome to Onchain Creator Summit‚Äîa hub for content creators, artists, and builders to collaborate, learn, and expand their impact onchain. 

The creator economy is evolving fast, and onchain tools are unlocking new ways to grow, monetize, and connect like never before. This all-day event is your backstage pass to the future of content creation. Whether you're a writer, artist, streamer, or community builder, you‚Äôll get hands-on access to the most powerful onchain tools‚Äîand the experts behind them.

Presented by CryptoSapiens in partnership with Vibe Check for a full day of programming. We invite you to join us for a day of connection and learning. Immerse yourself with select creators and web3 builders over coffee and snacks followed by a series of roundtable discussions.

12:00 PM - 1:00 PM: Networking & Coffee 

Come connect with peers and industry experts over a cup of hand-crafted coffee and light snacks [presented by Unlock Protocol]

1:00 PM - 3:00 PM: Roundtable Discussions

Join pioneering creators to explore how Web3 tools and token strategies are revolutionizing content creation, distribution, and community building - from leveraging platforms like Farcaster and Rodeo to implementing token incentives that drive sustainable growth and engagement

- Building the Future of Content Development with Web3 Tools
- The Secrets to Content Discoverability and Virality
- Tokenizing Creativity: Monetizing Content Onchain
-  Unlocking Community Loyalty with Tokenized Incentives

3:30 PM - 2:00 AM: Vibe Check 3.0 programming continues with lunch, cocktails and music.

GM Farcaster ep218 Monday February 24, 2025 with @polymarket intern
text:
Tokenization of everything could be good if we build infrastructure for tokens that allow them to be bought, sold, and used in a "good" way. 

I don't know what good means, which is why I'm not saying the Zora update is good or bad, but I think it has something to do with the messaging and UX around "content coins."

Highly curated NFT marketplaces *felt* better to me than high-speed attention markets, and I'm trying to figure out if the latter is truly good and something we want to optimize for explicitly.

cast.text: Still trying to develop a thesis around the new Zora update and ‚Äúcontent coins,‚Äù but I find it very off-putting that so many people are all-in on this shift with no coherent thesis of their own.
